fields.author: Malquidis
fields.message: I have spent way too much time already trying to dial in my C-ray emitters. I meshed my LPI with the view-screen auditor and got a count of 5. There are supposed to be 8. Honestly, a directional beam doesn't detect any. I need guidance.

fields.author: AcctDept
fields.message: Well, one of the first things you are going to want to get is an Aflogian-Cell 8 processing glastino at a decent mesh rate. Remember, if you can’t find a working Maury-Davis replica regener device, no one expects your C-Ray emitter to get over 7 without a duvine manipulation matrix giving you the appropriate bio-deflation reading.

fields.author: Golden_Funk
fields.message: Completely disconnect your power supply and wait a full 15 minutes before plugging it back in; then attempt to redial. Those old emitters take a long time to hard reset, and you're probably counting old tests instead of your current test. I can't say for sure if this will be your fix, but it's easy, so you should try it before anything else.
